Explain the graph in details, specifically describe the trade off between the learning rate and n jobs. Also comment on the evolution of error for each combination(1 paragraph at least, 1.5).¶

The five quadrant plot graphs the trend of Gradient Boosting accuracy scores as the increase of learning rate from 0.01 to 1. The Gradient Boosting's accuracy goes up as the increase of learning rate, with almost has no overfitting issue. The highest accuracy happens when learning rate = 0.11. Higher n_estimators (500) shows higher accuracy than low estimators (5) for 0.11 learning rate. This means there is trade-off between n_estimators. When we set up a low learning rate, there needs more training iterations to achieve optimal accuracy.¶
